item.title: 508 - Simple examine
item.dc:creator: @Sup22211 Sup22211
item.description:
@Sup22211 wrote:

So i downloaded a 508 source and it had nothing, so i wanted to add a examine:
1.Goto io-packetManager.java.
2.Change/add this case;

case 84:
int objectId = p.stream.readUnsignedWordA();
objectExamine(p, objectId);
break;

All it does is using a method that i am going to create.
the method:
3.add this method;

public void objectExamine(Player p, int oID){
switch(oID){
case 1276:
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "A tree.");
break;
		}
	}

A little explanation so you know how to add new examines;
“case 1276:” is a tree object id so what its saying: if i click examine then if its find the object id (1276) it will send the message “A tree” so if you want to add another one do this:
case objectID:
p.frames.sendMessage(p, “The message.”);
break;//closing the case
Good luck…

Now with a little helpful update, in the objectExamine method you can add:
default:
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "Unused object id: "+oID);
break;
With this any object you didn’t add a examine text it will send you a message of this objectID so you it will be easier to find object ids.
